                        <additions>
                          <list>
                            <item xml:id="a1"><locus from="1r" to="1v">Fols 1r–1v</locus>
                              <desc type="PoemSalam"><ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2835RepCh119">Mälkǝʾ-hymn to St Michael (Chaine nr. 119)</ref>, written in an inaccurate hand. The words ሰላም፡ and ሚካኤል፡ are rubricated. The text is incomplete</desc>
                              <q xml:lang="gez">ሰላም፡ ለዝክረ፡ ስምከ፡ ምስለ፡ ስመ፡ ልዑል፡ ዘተሳተፈ። ወልደ፡ ያሬድ፡ ሄኖክ፡ በከመ፡ ጸሐፈ፡ ሶበ፡ እጼ(ውዕ፡) ስመከ፡ ከሲትየ፡ አፈ፡ ረዳኤ።</q>
                          </item>
                            <item xml:id="a2"><locus from="156r" to="156v">Fols 156r–156v</locus>
                            <desc type="ScribalNoteCommissioning">Note on the commission of the manuscript, written in Amharic. It mentions the commissioner Aläqa Wäldä Śǝllase and the recipient Lǝǧǧ Abärra Nǝguse. </desc>
                            
                            <q xml:lang="am">መጋቢት፡ ፲፩ቀን፡ አለቃ፡ ወልደ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ለልጅ፡ አበራ፡ ንጉሴ፡ የብራና፡ ዳዊት፡ ሲሸጥ፡ እማኝ፡ ቄስ፡ ኪዳኑ፡ የልጅ፡ አበራ፡ የሸቃ፡. ተእምራ(156v)ት፡ መድህን፡ አለቃ፡ ሐደረ፡ በሶስት፡ ብር፡ ታላድ፡ ሶሽጥ፡ በሶስት፡ ብር፡ ታላድ፡ ሺገዛ፡ ፈጣሚ፡ ብላ፡ ገብሩ፡</q>
                          </item>
                          <item xml:id="e1">
                            <locus target="#2rv">Fol. 2rv</locus>
                            <p>Pen trials.</p>
                          </item>
                          
                        </list>
                        </additions>

                        <bindingDesc>
                          <binding contemporary="true" xml:id="binding">
                            <decoNote xml:id="b1">The book is sewn on four sewing stations (two pairs) linked to wooden boards covered with blind-tooled leather.</decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                           <material key="leather"/>
                        </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Cover">
                              The cover is made of a brown-reddish leather decorated with blind tooled motifs. The design shows a central latin cross surrounded by three rectangular frames.
                              The cross is composed by the repetition of the <term key="motherOfWater" ana="#motherOfWater">mother of water</term> motif. The outer and the inner frames are composed by the impression of a <term key="XForm" ana="#XForm">X-Form</term> tool.
                              The frame in the middle is empty and delimitated by <term key="singleStraightLine" ana="#singleStraightLine">single straight lines.</term> The single straight lines decorate also the turn-ins where they are crossed forming a "X" shape.
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b5" type="Endbands">
                              The codex doesn't have endbands but there are traces of tiedowns made of thread of animal origin.
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b6" type="SewingStations">4</decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b7">
                              The sewing is a chain-stitch on four sewing stations (two pairs). The sewing pattern is a variation of the <term key="patternA" ana="#patternA">pattern A</term> by Bozzacchi.
                              Along the fold of the first quire, for each pair of sewing station there is one long stitch with a knot. In the second quire there are two long stitches.
                              The thread used for the sewing is of <term key="animalThread" ana="#animalThread">animal origin</term>. The sewing has been repaired using stripes of parchment.
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b9" type="Spine">
                              The spine of the leather cover has been removed, probably in order to repair the sewing.
                            </decoNote>
                          </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
                      </physDesc>

